'''Drenth''' ({{IPA-nl|ˈdrɛnt}}) is a [[Dutch language|Dutch]] [[toponymic surname]] indicating an origin in the province of [[Drenthe]].<ref>[http://www.cbgfamilienamen.nl/nfb/detail_naam.php?gba_lcnaam=drenth&gba_naam=Drenth&nfd_naam=Drenth&operator=eq&taal= Drenth] at the Database of Surnames in The Netherlands.</ref> Variant forms are ''Drent'', ''Drenthe'', ''Drenthen'' and ''Van Drenth''. People with this surname include:
*[[Elt Drenth]] (1949–1998), Dutch freestyle swimmer *[[Herman Drenth]] (1892–1932), Dutch-American serial killer known as "Harry Powers" *[[Jan Drenth]] (born 1925), Dutch chemist *[[Maxim Februari|Max Drenth]] (born 1963), Dutch writer, philosopher and columnist known as "Maxim Februari" ;Drent *[[Ido Drent]] (born 1987), South African actor in New Zealand *[[Martin Drent]] (born 1970), Dutch football striker ;Drenthe *[[Eugène Drenthe]] (1925–2009), Surinamese poet and playwright *[[Giovanni Drenthe]] (born 1990), Surinamese football striker *[[Royston Drenthe]] (born 1987), Dutch football winger and rapper
