[[Image:Sudan political map 2000.jpg|thumb|right|Political map of Sudan. [[Hala'ib Triangle]] has been under Egyptian administration since 2000.]] {{Main|States of Sudan|Districts of Sudan|Counties of Sudan}} [[Sudan]] is divided into [[States of Sudan|fifteen states]] (''[[wilaya]]t'', [[Grammatical number|sing.]] ''[[wilayah]]'') which in turn are subdivided into [[Districts of Sudan|86 districts]]. Before the secession of [[South Sudan]] on July 9, 2011, Sudan was the largest country in Africa and had 25 states.
